{
  "texts": [
    "The difference between ANS and Baly et al. [98] is that ANS generated fake and true claims from true news.",
    "In the same vein, the AraStance dataset [99] contained 4,063 pairs of claims and articles from multiple countries, covering topics in politics, health, sports, and others.",
    "The annotation process was performed manually according to the veracity of the claims, whether they are true or false, and according to the article\"s stance on the claims, which ended with four labels: agree, disagree, discuss, and unrelated.",
    "Satirical News [89] is a hand-built dataset that includes fake articles.",
    "The fake news articles were collected from two satirical news websites: Al-Hudood 15 and Al-Ahram Al-Mexici 16."
  ]
}